{#def count="" #}
{#
  Notification badge. One component, two shapes, chosen by whether ``count``
  is set (Figma node 330-4472):

    - dot (default; ``count`` empty) -- an 8px solid ``important`` circle,
      vertically centered. The bare "there's something new" indicator; this is
      what the titlebar requests button shows today.
    - count (``count`` set) -- a solid ``important`` pill with the number in the
      white bold ``type-badge`` role (10 / 12). ``min-w-[16px]`` keeps a single
      digit circular and it grows horizontally for wider numbers ("12"); counts
      above 99 collapse to "99+". Not wired into the live app yet -- demoed in
      the styleguide.

  The badge carries no position of its own (a reusable component owns no outer
  offset): the caller places it. The titlebar pins the dot to the messages
  button's top-right corner with ``class="absolute top-0.5 right-0.5"`` and
  toggles ``class="hidden"`` from chrome.js. Any undeclared HTML attribute
  (id=, class=, data-*) flows through JinjaX ``attrs``; ``class="..."`` is
  appended to the component's canonical class set.
#}
{%- if count == "" -%}
<span {{ attrs.render(classes="inline-block align-middle w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-important") }}></span>
{%- else -%}
{%- set _n = count | int -%}
<span {{ attrs.render(classes="inline-flex items-center justify-center align-middle min-w-[16px] px-1 py-px rounded-full bg-important text-white type-badge whitespace-nowrap overflow-hidden") }}>{{ "99+" if _n > 99 else _n }}</span>
{%- endif -%}
